.TH SGDRM-TEXT 1 "2026-05-07" "SGUTILS 2.0.0" "Screen Graphics Utilities"
.SH NAME
sgdrm-text \- render text on a DRM/KMS display using TrueType fonts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sgdrm-text
\fB-t\fR \fITEXT\fR \fB-F\fR \fIFONT\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sgdrm-text
renders text directly to a DRM/KMS display using any TrueType or OpenType font.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -t ", " --text " " \fISTRING\fR
(Required) Text to render.
.TP
.BR -F ", " --font " " \fIPATH\fR
(Required) Path to a .ttf or .otf font file.
.TP
.BR -d ", " --device " " \fIPATH\fR
DRM device (default: /dev/dri/card0).
.TP
.BR -s ", " --size " " \fIN\fR
Font size in pixels (default: 32).
.TP
.BR -x ", " --xpos " " \fIN\fR
X position (default: 0).
.TP
.BR -y ", " --ypos " " \fIN\fR
Y baseline position (default: font size).
.TP
.BR -c ", " --color " " \fIRRGGBB\fR
Text color in hex (default: FFFFFF).
.TP
.BR -b ", " --bg-color " " \fIRRGGBB\fR
Fill background before text.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help message.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ sgdrm-text -t "Hello" -F /usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu/DejaVuSans.ttf
$ sgdrm-text -t "Status" -F /path/to/font.ttf -s 64 -c 00FF00
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sgfb-text (1),
.BR sgdrm-describe (1)

